Hannah Okonkwo is Obi's mother, Hannah, is another woman of strong-will in the novel, with whom Obi has a special relationship. It is Obi's mother that refuses to allow him to marry Clara by threat of her own suicide. However, it was also Hannah that shared folk stories with Obiâ€”stories that he could share at school and for which he loved her. They also have a special bond of blood, according to a story in which his mother cuts herself with a blade from his pocket.